from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(s: str) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    i = 0   # --- py stmt 3
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 4
    chars = set()   # --- py stmt 5
    for j, c in enumerate(s):   # --- py stmt 6
        if c == ' ':   # --- py stmt 7
            continue   # --- py stmt 8
        elif c == '*':   # --- py stmt 9
            break   # --- py stmt 10
        while c in chars:   # --- py stmt 11
            chars.remove(s[i])   # --- py stmt 12
            i += 1   # --- py stmt 13
        chars.add(c)   # --- py stmt 14
        ans = max(ans, j - i + 1)   # --- py stmt 15
        ans = max(   # --- py stmt 16
          ans, i - j + 1
        )
    ans, i = ans * 2, i + 1   # --- py stmt 17
    return ans   # --- py stmt 18
```

### countSquares 
from typing import *   # --- py stmt 1
def f_gold(matrix: List[List[int]]) -> int:   # --- py stmt 2
    m, n = len(matrix), len(matrix[0])   # --- py stmt 3
    f = [[0] * n for _ in range(m)]   # --- py stmt 4
    ans = 0   # --- py stmt 5
    for i, row in enumerate(matrix):   # --- py stmt 6
        for j, v in enumerate(row):   # --- py stmt 7
            if v == 0:   # --- py stmt 8
                continue   # --- py stmt 9
            if i == 0 or j == 0:   # --- py stmt 10
                f[i][j] = 1   # --- py stmt 11
            else:   # --- py stmt 12
                f[i][j] = min(f[i - 1][j - 1], f[i - 1][j], f[i][j - 1]) + 1   # --- py stmt 13
            ans += f[i][j]   # --- py stmt 14
    return ans   # --- py stmt 15
```

function countSquares(matrix) {   // --- py stmt 2
    const m = matrix.length;   // --- py stmt 3
    const n = matrix[0].length;   // --- py stmt 3
    const f = Array.from({ length: m }, () => Array(n).fill(0));   // --- py stmt 4
    let ans = 0;   // --- py stmt 5
    for (let i = 0; i < m; i++) {   // --- py stmt 6
        const row = matrix[i];   // --- py stmt 7
        for (let j = 0; j < n; j++) {   // --- py stmt 7
            const v = row[j];   // --- py stmt 7
            if (v === 0) {   // --- py stmt 8
                continue;   // --- py stmt 9
            }
            if (i === 0 || j === 0) {   // --- py stmt 10
                f[i][j] = 1;   // --- py stmt 11
            } else {   // --- py stmt 12
                f[i][j] = Math.min(f[i - 1][j - 1], f[i - 1][j], f[i][j - 1]) + 1;   // --- py stmt 13
            }
            ans += f[i][j];   // --- py stmt 14
        }
    }
    return ans;   // --- py stmt 15
}
